Moreover, the market segmentation by therapy type, specifically Enzyme Replacement Therapy (ERT) and Hematopoietic Stem Cell Transplantation (HSCT), highlights the diverse treatment modalities available to LAL-D patients. ERT, being the most common therapy utilized, involves the administration of recombinant LAL enzyme to compensate for the deficient enzyme activity in patients. On the other hand, HSCT offers a more complex but potentially curative approach by transplanting healthy stem cells to restore enzyme function. The availability of these treatment options underscores the evolving landscape of LAL-D management and underscores the importance of personalized care in addressing the unique needs of each patient.

